6 district's foundation allowance as provided in this section, using
7 a target foundation allowance in the amount specified in subsection
8 (1).
9 (3) Except as otherwise provided in this section, the
10 department shall calculate the amount of a district's foundation
11 allowance as follows, using in all calculations the total amount of
12 the district's foundation allowance as calculated before any
13 proration:
14 (a) For a district that had a foundation allowance for the
15 immediately preceding fiscal year that was equal to the target
16 foundation allowance for the immediately preceding fiscal year, the
17 district receives a foundation allowance in an amount equal to the
18 target foundation allowance described in subsection (1) for the
19 current fiscal year.
20 (b) For a district that had a foundation allowance for the
21 immediately preceding fiscal year that was greater than the target
22 foundation allowance for the immediately preceding fiscal year, the
23 district's foundation allowance is an amount equal to the lesser of
24 (the sum of the district's foundation allowance for the immediately
25 preceding fiscal year plus any per pupil amount calculated under
26 section 20m(2) in the immediately preceding fiscal year plus the
27 increase in the target foundation allowance for the current fiscal
28 year, as compared to the immediately preceding fiscal year) or (the
29 product of the district's foundation allowance for the immediately
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

62
1 preceding fiscal year times the percentage increase in the United
2 States Consumer Price Index in the calendar year ending in the
3 immediately preceding fiscal year as reported by the May revenue
4 estimating conference conducted under section 367b of the
5 management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1367b).
6 (c) For a district that had a foundation allowance in the
7 immediately preceding fiscal year that was less than the target
8 foundation allowance in effect for that fiscal year, the district's
9 foundation allowance is an amount equal to the lesser of (the sum
10 of district's foundation allowance for the immediately preceding
11 fiscal year plus any per pupil amount calculated under section
12 20m(2) in the immediately preceding fiscal year plus the increase
13 in the target foundation allowance for the current fiscal year, as
14 compared to the immediately preceding fiscal year) or (the product
15 of the district's foundation allowance for the immediately
16 preceding fiscal year times the percentage increase in the United
17 States Consumer Price Index in the calendar year ending in the
18 immediately preceding fiscal year as reported by the May revenue
19 estimating conference conducted under section 367b of the
20 management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1367b).
21 (d) For a district that has a foundation allowance that is not
22 a whole dollar amount, the department shall round the district's
23 foundation allowance up to the nearest whole dollar.
24 (4) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, the state
25 portion of a district's foundation allowance is an amount equal to
26 the district's foundation allowance or the target foundation
