6 submit the report to the house and senate appropriations
7 subcommittees on school aid, the state budget director, the house
8 and senate fiscal agencies, the department, districts, and
9 intermediate districts by not later than March 31 of each fiscal
10 year for which funding is allocated under this section.
11 (v) Provide an extensive professional development program to
12 at least 30,000 educational personnel, including teachers, school
13 administrators, and school board members, that focuses on the
14 effective integration of virtual learning into curricula and
15 instruction. The Michigan Virtual Learning Research Institute is
16 encouraged to work with the MiSTEM council described in section 99s
