6 under this subsection must be estimated and charged in increments
7 of 15 minutes or more, with all partial time increments rounded
8 down. When calculating costs under subsection (4), fee components
9 must be itemized in a manner that expresses both the hourly wage
10 and the number of hours charged. The nonpublic school may not
11 charge any applicable labor charge amount to cover or partially
12 cover the cost of health or fringe benefits. A nonpublic school
13 shall not charge any overtime wages in the calculation of labor
14 costs.
