19 Sec. 164k. If the department receives a report that a district
20 or intermediate district is violating any of the following
21 requirements, and the department confirms the violation, the
22 department shall withhold 5% of the payment the district is
23 eligible to receive under section 22b, or 5% of the payment the
24 intermediate district is eligible to receive under section 81, as
25 applicable, for as long as the district or intermediate district is
26 out of compliance:
27 (a) A district or intermediate district shall ensure that all
28 food made available to a student in the breakfast or lunch program
29 complies with all federal rules and regulations related to school
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

397
1 meals.
2 (b) To the extent practicable under federal regulations, a
3 district or intermediate district shall require each student
4 household to complete the child nutrition and education benefits
5 application, as provided by the department, for free and reduced-
6 price school meals regardless of whether the district or
7 intermediate district opts to provide universal breakfast or lunch.
8 (c) For pupil membership count days after the fall 2025 count,
9 a district or intermediate district shall not provide a financial
10 incentive to students for attending pupil membership count day.
11 (d) A district or intermediate district shall ensure that
12 student survey questions and results are made available to the
13 public, posted on the district's or intermediate district's
14 website, and that parents and legal guardians are notified of the
15 survey. As used in this subsection, "survey" includes any survey
16 from the district or intermediate district or from the local,
17 state, or federal government.
18 (e) Beginning with the fiscal year ending September 30, 2026,
19 if a district is not using a curriculum from the department's
20 evidence-based curriculum list required under section 1280f of the
21 revised school code, MCL 380.1280f, the district must provide a
22 notification to all parents or legal guardians of students in
23 grades K to 5 receiving instruction with that curriculum that
24 includes all of the following:
25 (i) A statement informing parents or legal guardians that the
26 curriculum used by the district is not evidence-based or not
27 aligned to state standards, which could negatively impact student
28 academic outcomes.
