9 Sec. 201i. (1) Not later than 30 days after the enactment of
10 the amendatory act that added this section, the legislature shall
11 provide to the responsible entity and the state budget director a
12 list of legislatively directed spending items, which may be
13 referred to in this section as grants or direct appropriation
14 grants, funded under the amendatory act that added this section
15 consistent with house or senate rules and this section. The list
16 must include all information and documents pertaining to the funded
17 items as publicly disclosed in accordance with house or senate
18 rules and this section.
19 (2) Notwithstanding any other conditions or requirements for
20 direct appropriation grants, the responsible entity shall perform,
21 at a minimum, at least all of the following activities to
22 administer the grants described in subsection (1):
23 (a) Establish a process to review, complete, and execute a
24 grant agreement with a grant recipient. The responsible entity
25 shall not execute a grant agreement unless all necessary
26 documentation has been submitted and reviewed.
27 (b) Verify to the extent possible that a grant recipient is a
28 not-for-profit entity and will use funds as publicly disclosed and
29 for a public purpose that serves the economic prosperity, health,
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

