1 safety, or general welfare of the residents of this state.
2 (c) Review and verify all necessary information to ensure the
3 grant recipient is reasonably able to execute the grant agreement,
4 perform its fiduciary duty, and comply with all applicable state
5 and federal statutes. The responsible entity may deduct the cost of
6 background checks and any other efforts performed as part of this
7 verification from the amount of the designated grant award.
8 (d) Disburse the grant money per the grant disbursement
9 schedule in the executed grant agreement on a reimbursement basis
10 after the grantee has provided sufficient documentation, as
11 determined by the responsible entity, to verify that expenditures
12 were made in accordance with the project purpose.
13 (e) If the state budget director determines that information
14 provided by the grantee does not meet the disclosure requirements,
15 that the grant will be used to pay a tax lien, delinquent tax, or
16 other obligation owed to this state, or that the grant will create
17 a conflict of interest, the responsible entity shall not release
18 the grant money to the grantee. Money that is not released under
19 this subdivision lapses at the end of the fiscal year. There is not
20 a conflict of interest if the sponsoring legislator certifies that
21 the sponsoring legislator's immediate family members, legislative
22 staff members that have worked for the sponsoring legislator within
23 the past 2 years, and the sponsoring legislator do not have a
24 direct or indirect pecuniary interest in the legislatively directed
25 spending item.
