10 Sec. 210. (1) Recognizing the critical importance of education
11 in strengthening Michigan's workforce, each community college is
12 encouraged to shall explore ways of increasing collaboration and
13 cooperation with 4-year universities, particularly in the areas
14 related to training, instruction, and program articulation.
15 (2) Recognizing the central role of community colleges in
16 responding to local employment needs and challenges, community
17 colleges shall develop and continue efforts to collaborate with
18 local employers and students to identify local employment needs and
19 strategies to meet them.
20 (3) Community colleges are encouraged to shall collaborate
21 with each other on innovations to identify and meet local
22 employment needs.
23 (4) Community colleges are encouraged to shall work with
24 universities to develop equivalency standards of core college
25 courses and identify equivalent courses offered by postsecondary
26 institutions.
27 Sec. 210b. By March 1 of each year, the Michigan Community
28 College Association and the Michigan Association of State
29 Universities shall submit a report to the senate and house
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

