1 regarding transfer credits and transfer students.
2 Sec. 212. Community college districts are encouraged to
3 evaluate and pursue efficiency and cost-containment measures that
4 maximize state funding. Community colleges shall identify practices
5 that increase efficiencies, including, but not limited to,
6 establishing joint ventures, consolidating services, utilizing
7 program collaborations, maximizing educational benefits through
8 optimal class sizes and frequency of course offerings, increasing
9 web-based instruction, eliminating low-enrollment and high-cost
10 instructional programs, using self-insurance, practicing energy
11 conservation, and utilizing group purchasing. Community colleges
12 shall also review proposed capital outlay projects to increase
13 coordination and utilization of new facilities, renovation
14 projects, and technology improvements.
