17 Sec. 241h. It is the intent of the legislature that taxpayer
18 funds appropriated under this article are to be used to educate
19 public university students and continue maintenance of public
20 university buildings and other assets. The goal of the legislature
21 is that taxpayer funds not be used excessively for administration.
22 Therefore, a public university that receives an appropriation under
23 this article shall not spend more than 10% of that appropriation on
24 administration. A sum of money spent in excess of the 10% cap
25 described in this section by a public university results in a
26 forfeiture of an amount equal to 50% of that sum from funds
27 appropriated to that public university, not to exceed the total
28 amount appropriated to that public university under this article.
29 The auditor general may investigate allegations of violations of
