19 Sec. 276. (1) Included in the appropriation for fiscal year
20 2024-2025 2025-2026 for each public university in section 236 is
21 funding for the Martin Luther King, Jr. - Cesar Chavez - Rosa Parks
22 future faculty fellowship program that is intended to increase the
23 pool of academically or economically disadvantaged candidates
24 pursuing faculty or administration careers in postsecondary
25 education in this state. Preference may not be given to applicants
26 on the basis of race, color, ethnicity, gender, or national origin.
27 Institutions should encourage applications from applicants who
28 would otherwise not adequately be represented in the graduate
29 student, faculty, or administration populations. Each public
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

505
1 university shall apply the percentage change applicable to every
2 public university in the calculation of appropriations in section
3 236 to the amount of funds allocated to the future faculty
4 fellowship program.
5 (2) Each public university shall administer the program in a
6 manner prescribed by the department of labor and economic
7 opportunity. The department of labor and economic opportunity shall
8 use a good-faith effort standard to evaluate whether a fellowship
9 is in default. All of the following apply to the program:
10 (a) By June 15 of each year, public universities shall report
11 any anticipated unexpended or unencumbered program funds to the
12 department of labor and economic opportunity. Encumbered funds are
13 those funds that were committed by a fellowship agreement that is
14 signed during the current fiscal year or administrative expenses
15 that have been approved by the department of labor and economic
16 opportunity.
17 (b) Before September 1 of each year, unexpended or
18 unencumbered funds may be transferred, under the direction of the
19 department of labor and economic opportunity, to a future faculty
20 fellowship program at another public university to be awarded to an
21 eligible candidate at that public university.
22 (c) Program allocations not expended or encumbered by
23 September 30, 2026 2027 must be returned to the department of labor
24 and economic opportunity so that those funds may lapse to the state
25 general fund.
26 (d) Not more than 5% of each public university's allocation
27 for the program may be used for administration of the program.
28 (e) In addition to the appropriation for fiscal year 2024-
29 2025, 2025-2026, any revenue received during prior fiscal years by
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

506
1 the department of labor and economic opportunity from defaulted
2 fellowship agreements is appropriated for the purposes originally
