4 Sec. 277. (1) Included in the appropriation for fiscal year
5 2024-2025 2025-2026 for each public university in section 236 is
6 funding for the Martin Luther King, Jr. - Cesar Chavez - Rosa Parks
7 college day program that is intended to introduce academically or
8 economically disadvantaged schoolchildren to the potential of a
9 college education in this state. Preference may not be given to
10 participants on the basis of race, color, ethnicity, gender, or
11 national origin. Public universities should encourage participation
12 from those who would otherwise not adequately be represented in the
13 student population.
14 (2) Individual program plans of each public university must
15 include a budget of equal contributions from this program, the
16 participating public university, the participating school district,
17 and the participating independent degree-granting college. College
18 day funds must not be expended to cover indirect costs. Not more
19 than 20% of the university match may be attributable to indirect
20 costs. Each public university shall apply the percentage change
21 applicable to every public university in the calculation of
22 appropriations in section 236 to the amount of funds allocated to
23 the college day program.
24 (3) Each public university shall administer the program
25 described in this section in a manner prescribed by the department
26 of labor and economic opportunity.
27 Sec. 278. (1) Included in the appropriation for fiscal year
28 2024-2025 2025-2026 for each public university in section 236 is
29 funding for the Martin Luther King, Jr. - Cesar Chavez - Rosa Parks
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

