8 Sec. 283. (1) Using the data provided to the center as
9 required by section 244 of this act, the center shall use the P-20
10 longitudinal data system to inform interested Michigan high schools
11 and the public regarding the aggregate academic status of its
12 students. The center shall work with the public universities and
13 the Michigan Association of State Universities and in cooperation
14 with the Michigan Association of Secondary School Principals.
15 (2) Michigan high schools shall systematically inform the
16 public universities about the use of information received under
17 this section in a manner prescribed by the Michigan Association of
18 Secondary School Principals in cooperation with the Michigan
19 Association of State Universities.
20 (3) The center shall conduct a review of the statewide
21 longitudinal data system and associated data collection processes
22 to identify strategies that would allow for the legal dissemination
23 of student directory information for all students in grades 11 and
24 12 to Michigan public and independent nonprofit postsecondary
25 institutions. The center shall collaborate with relevant
26 stakeholders to recommend a process to share this data by June 30,
27 2024.
28 Sec. 284. Using data provided to the center as required by
29 section 244 of this act, the center shall use the P-20 longitudinal
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

511
1 data system to inform Michigan community colleges regarding the
2 academic status of community college transfer students. The center
3 shall work with the department of lifelong education, advancement,
4 and potential, the universities, and the Michigan Association of
5 State Universities in cooperation with the Michigan Community
6 College Association.
7 Sec. 285. From the funds appropriated in section 236(2),
8 public universities shall work with the state community colleges to
9 encourage the transfer of students from the community colleges to
10 the public universities and to facilitate the transfer of credits
11 from the community colleges to those public universities. Each
12 public university that receives an appropriation under section 236
13 shall consult with the department of lifelong education,
14 advancement, and potential at least once an academic year on the
15 policies and services the institution implements regarding transfer
16 credits and transfer students.
17 Sec. 286. From the funds appropriated in section 236(2),
18 public universities shall work with community colleges in this
19 state to implement statewide reverse transfer agreements to
20 increase the number of students that are awarded credentials of
21 value upon completion of the necessary credits. These statewide
22 agreements shall enable students who have earned a significant
23 number of credits at a community college and transfer to a
24 baccalaureate granting institution before completing a degree to
25 transfer the credits earned at the baccalaureate institution back
26 to the community college in order to be awarded a credential of
27 value. Each public university that receives an appropriation under
28 section 236 shall consult with the department of lifelong
29 education, advancement, and potential at least once an academic
CRM S01533'25 (S-3) CR-1 mposkv

